{"article_id":"M4njfUlXlul5VuW4","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" The Supreme Court is the highest court in the nation ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"and it said","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that it ' s a tax ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"so it ' s a tax , \"","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Mr. Romney told CBS News .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"\" They have spoken .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"There ' s no way around that. \"","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"He later repeated his assertion to CNN after a Fourth of July parade here , an idyllic summer retreat on the edge of Lake Winnipesaukee .","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"The Obama campaign seized on Mr. Romney ' s words ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"calling it a glaring contradiction of his chief spokesman ' s remarks .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"\" First , he threw his top aide Eric Fehrnstrom under the bus","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"by changing his campaign ' s position , \"","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the campaign said .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"\" Second , he contradicted himself","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"by saying","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"his own Massachusetts mandate wasn ' t a tax . \"","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Mr. Fehrnstrom ' s comments on Monday ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"in which he also said","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"that Mr. Romney felt","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the health care law was unconstitutional","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and should have been invalidated ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"were backed up by a campaign news release that day","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"that Mr. Romney believed","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"the mandate is \" an unconstitutional penalty \" - notably , not a tax .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"The backlash","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"that erupted on Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"was a reminder of just how problematic the issue of health care reform is for Mr. Romney .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"As governor of Massachusetts , he oversaw the 2007 fulfillment of a first-in-the-nation plan","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"requiring","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"that nearly every state resident obtain health insurance","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"or pay a penalty","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"if they failed to do so .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"The question of the \" individual mandate , \"","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"as the requirement is known ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"has emerged as one of the most polarizing national political issues of the day .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"It helped propel the Tea Party movement to mainstream politics ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"with conservatives calling it a gross overreach of federal power and an infringement on personal liberty .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Mr. Romney ' s support of the Massachusetts plan deepened suspicions among many conservatives ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"who were already wary of him","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"because of the more liberal positions","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he once took on social issues like abortion and gay rights .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Please verify","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Sign Up","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":3},{"id":60,"text":"His comments about the mandate being a tax","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"came on an otherwise slow Fourth of July ,","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"ensuring","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"that they dominated the news cycle ,","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"albeit one","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"that fewer people than usual were paying attention to .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"By insisting","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"the mandate is a tax ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Mr. Romney has opened himself up to the criticism","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"that he , too , raised taxes as governor .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"His campaign has sought to portray him as a tax cutter ,","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"despite the Obama campaign ' s efforts","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to highlight state fees","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that rose under Mr. Romney .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"In the CBS interview , he insisted","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"that he had not imposed a tax","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"and sought to draw an academic distinction between taxes and penalties .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" The chief justice in his opinion made it very clear","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"that at the state level , states have the power","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"to put in place mandates , \"","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"\" And as a result , Massachusetts ' s mandate was a mandate ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"was a penalty ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"was described that way by the legislature and by me ,","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"and so it stays","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"as it was . \"","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"Mr. Romney appeared to be making a finer point about the absolute role","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"the Supreme Court plays","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"in setting American law ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"even if the nuance was lost on many .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"\" Well , the Supreme Court has the final word","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"and their final word is that Obamacare is a tax .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"So it ' s a tax , \"","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"He also sought to reconcile his comments on Wednesday with his earlier positions","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"- and put himself in line with conservatives -","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"by saying","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"he agreed with the dissent in the Supreme Court case .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"That dissent , by Anthony M. Kennedy and three more conservative justices","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"- Clarence Thomas , Antonin Scalia and Samuel A. Alito Jr. -","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"called the majority ' s ruling \" vast judicial overreach \"","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"and argued","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"that the health care law should have been struck down .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"Bill Burton , a founder of Priorities USA Action , a \" super PAC \"","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"supporting Mr. Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"that \" Romney ' s ideological gymnastics will both weaken his standing on the health care debate","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"but , more importantly , will further undercut any notion of strength in his leadership . \"","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Romney ' s remarks proved a distraction from what should have been a day of patriotic photo-ops","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"as he vacationed in New Hampshire .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"He appeared in the annual Fourth of July parade here ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"energetically working the crowds .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"\" Terrific to see you ! \"","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"beaming","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"as he stretched his hands out toward the onlookers ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"sometimes shaking with both hands .","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"\" Hey , how are you ?","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"Happy Fourth of July ! \"","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"Though this is clearly Romney country","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"- yard signs for the candidate dot lawns everywhere here , the site of his lake house -","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"there were a few interlopers along the parade route .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"Sid Hall of nearby Tuftonboro stood with a group of his friends and family","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"waving \" New Hampshire for Obama \" signs along Main Street .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"About 20 of them were at the parade , a family ritual","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"that is usually apolitical .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"But this year","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"he said","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"they decided to pull a quiet act of liberal defiance .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"\" We do feel a little out of our element , \"","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"he said with a smile .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":261,"left":172,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":138,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":137,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":135,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":134,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":0,"right":133,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":3,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":132,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":136,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":154,"right":17